item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:

Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)

...or something like this:

The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.

As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: Home
item.dc:creator: abhishek
item.content:encoded:
Welcome to the digital hub of innovation and expertise. Here, in the heart of my portfolio, you'll find the culmination of my dedication to the ever-evolving world of IT engineering. From intricate coding marvels to seamless system integrations, each project represents a testament to my commitment to excellence. Join me on a journey through the intricate networks of technology, where problem-solving meets creativity, and possibilities are limitless. Let's shape the future of IT together, one line of code at a time.


About Me

Abhishek Singh

I'm happy B.Tech student majoring in Information Technology, I approach my studies with enthusiasm and positivity. My proficiency in Java and Python allows me to tackle technical challenges with confidence, while my ability to communicate effectively ensures that concepts are easily understood by others. I'm always eager to broaden my knowledge and stay updated on the latest advancements in technology. With a natural knack for leadership, I thrive in fast-paced environments, where I excel at rallying teams together and guiding them through projects with a collaborative approach, resulting in exceptional outcomes.


Projects

PlantPedia

This project aims to assist farmers and agricultural professionals in identifying plant diseases by analyzing images of plant leaves. By employing machine learning techniques, we can accurately classify various types of diseases affecting plant leaves. Additionally, the project includes a user-friendly web interface built with React.js, allowing users to upload images and receive instant disease classification results.

Metro Management System

The Metro Management System is a software solution designed to streamline the operations and management of a metro rail system. This project leverages Java for backend logic and JavaServer Pages (JSP) for building dynamic web pages. The system aims to facilitate efficient ticket booking, route planning, and overall management of metro services.

Driver Drowsiness Detection

This project aims to enhance road safety by detecting driver drowsiness using machine learning techniques. Driver drowsiness is a significant factor in road accidents, and timely detection can prevent potentially fatal consequences. By leveraging machine learning algorithms, we can analyze facial features and driver behavior to accurately identify signs of drowsiness and issue alerts to the driver.

Projects


Education

 
Noida Institute Of Engineering and Technology, Greater Noida
Bachelor of Technology

September 2021 - July 2025

Participated in the research of Driver Drowsiness Detection and published 1 papers.

  • Driver Drowsiness Detection
 
Christ Jyoti Senior Secondary School
School(Nursery - 12th Standard)

April 2007 - April 2021

 


Experience

  • IT & Web Development Intern

     BasketHunt Private limited, Remote May 2024 - Current

  • Collaborated with the development team to integrate new features into the company’s web applications, such as a user-friendly checkout process and personalized recommendation engine, resulting in a 25 percent increase in user engagement.

  • Assisted in troubleshooting and resolving technical issues, ensuring the smooth operation of the company’s online platforms and maintaining a 99.9 percent uptime rate.

  •  

  • Web Development Intern

     Octanet Services Private limited, Remote February 2024 - April 2024

  • Developed a responsive website Ui using HTML, CSS and JavaScript that reduced overall page load speed by 15

  • Enhanced the usability of existing applications by applying the latest accessibility standards and best practices

  • Machine Learning Intern

    YBI foundation, Remote Sept 2022 - Nov 2022

  • Project (2022): Developed and evaluated a machine learning model using script learn to mobile price classification

  • Personal Project (2022): Built a plant leaf disease classifications application using tensor flow to analyze plant disease. The application achieved 85 percent accuracy


Technical Skills

Programming Languages: Python, Java, C, JavaScript, SQL

General: Data Structures and Algorithm, OOPs, OS, Git, Github, DBMS, Machine Learning

Database: Oracle, MySql, MongoDb and PostgreSql

Development: Wordpress, HTML, CSS, ReactJS, JSP.

Soft Skills:Strategic planning, strong commitment, self-driven, eagerness to contribute and problem-solving skills.


Achievements and Certifications

Data Structures and algorithm using python(Infosys)

Python (HackerRank)

item.dc:creator: abhishek
item.content:encoded:
Projects

PlantPedia (Plant leaf Disease Classification)

Tech:- Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Tensorflow, React.JS
This project aims to assist farmers and agricultural professionals in identifying plant diseases by analyzing images of plant leaves. Learn more

Driver Drowsiness Detection

Tech:- Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Tensorflow, React.js
This project aims to enhance road safety by detecting driver drowsiness using machine learning techniques and timely detection can prevent potentially fatal consequences. Learn more

Phishing Website Detection

Tech:- Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Tensorflow and CV2
This repository contains a machine learning-based approach to detecting phishing websites. Phishing websites are malicious sites that mimic legitimate ones to steal sensitive information such as usernames, passwords, and credit card details. Learn more

Metro Management System

Tech:- Java, Spring, Servlet, JSP, RestAPI
he Metro Management System is a software solution designed to streamline the operations and management of a metro rail system. This project leverages Java for backend logic and JavaServer Pages (JSP) for building dynamic web pages. Learn more

On Road Vehicle Breakdown Assistant

Tech:- HTML, CSS, Javascript, MySql
The On Road Vehicle Breakdown Assistant is a web application designed to provide assistance to drivers who encounter vehicle breakdowns while on the road. Learn more

News Web

Tech:- Python, Machine Learning, React.JS
This is a simple React application that fetches and displays news headlines from the News API. The headlines are displayed in a visually appealing format. Learn more

Movies Success Rate Prediction

Tech:- Data Analytics, Knime, Deep Learning
The aim is to predict if a movie will be profitable, given a variety of factors: popularity of actors, budget, country of production, etc. Learn more

Sales Dashboard

Tech:- Data Analytics, Tableau, Knime
The Aim of this project is to create a dashboard that will continuously fetch the data from the dataset and display in the form of charts, bar graph. Learn more

About Me

Abhishek Singh

Welcome! I’m thrilled to share a bit about myself. My name is Abhishek Singh, and I am currently pursuing a B.Tech in Information Technology. I approach my studies with enthusiasm and positivity, always eager to dive into the world of technology and innovation.

Technical Skills

I have a strong foundation in programming, particularly in Java and Python. These languages have become my tools of choice for solving complex problems and developing creative solutions. I enjoy the logical thinking and problem-solving aspects of programming, and I’m always on the lookout for new challenges to tackle.

Development

I also have hands-on experience in WordPress development, and full-stack development. We are a team of developers specializing in WordPress and full stack development, providing comprehensive web solutions from design to deployment, ensuring performance, security, and user-friendly experiences.

Communication

One of my key strengths is clear and effective communication. I believe that being able to explain complex technical concepts in a way that is understandable to others is crucial, whether I’m working with fellow students, collaborating with a team, or interacting with non-technical stakeholders. This skill has been instrumental in my academic and project success, allowing me to bridge gaps and ensure everyone is on the same page.

Leadership and Teamwork

Leadership comes naturally to me, and I excel in dynamic and fast-paced environments. I have successfully led teams through various projects and competitions, fostering a collaborative and supportive atmosphere. My approach to leadership is inclusive, ensuring that every team member feels valued and empowered to contribute their best. Together, we have achieved outstanding results, often exceeding expectations.

item.title: Privacy Policy
item.dc:creator: abhishek
item.content:encoded:
Who we are

Suggested text: Our website address is: https://abhishekportnietthakur.lovestoblog.com.

Comments

Suggested text: When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor’s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.

An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.

Media

Suggested text: If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.

Cookies

Suggested text: If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.

If you visit our login page, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.

When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select "Remember Me", your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.

If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.

Embedded content from other websites

Suggested text: Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.

These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.

Who we share your data with

Suggested text: If you request a password reset, your IP address will be included in the reset email.

How long we retain your data

Suggested text: If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.

For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.

What rights you have over your data

Suggested text: If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.

Where your data is sent

Suggested text: Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.

item.title: Projects
item.dc:creator: abhishek
item.content:encoded:
My Projects

A Glimpse into Our Projects

  • PlantPedia(Plant leaf disease classification), Worked on improving the plant web application fixing/highlighting potential issues and classify the plant disease classification. Pull Requests merged fixing existing disease , issues in theapplication,contributedtoserver-side. GitHub
  • LivoGo(Metro Management System), Innovated a Full Stack Software-as-a-Service web Application to book online metro ticket reservation. Developed a network for tracking of any nearest metro from any particular metro station. Incorporated Transaction/communication using RazorPayAPI and Firestore, with eforts to increase income andpresence. Tryit!
  • On road vehicle breakdown help assistant , • Made a website for any driver need help or any mechanic in between their rides. • If anyone needs help related to vehichle we track the location and directly contact to the nearestmechanic.•IncorporatedTransaction/communicationusingRazorPay. GitHub
